  <prompt>
    Build the `FilePreviewContextWidget` — a NEW Context-pane widget that renders
    inline (non-modal) file previews for the R5 chat-driven Summarize vertical
    slice. The widget WRAPS the extracted `RichFilePreview` renderer (produced by
    task 013); it MUST NOT rebuild iframe/metadata/navigation/menu logic. In
    single-file mode the widget renders the active file inline. In multi-file
    mode the widget renders a list of file cards above the active preview;
    clicking a card swaps the active file and emits a `context.file_selected`
    PaneEventBus event (additive type added by task 016).

    The per-file 3-dot menu reuses the existing `DocumentRowMenu` shared
    component (12 actions in canonical FR-DOC-01 order). For R5 the relevant
    actions are `aiSummary` (triggers Summarize playbook), `toggleWorkspace`
    (pin to Workspace), and `findSimilar` (existing RAG flow). Other actions
    are wired through `onAction` to the host's dispatcher; non-applicable
    actions may be passed via `disabledActions`.

    This widget is the Context-pane counterpart to the upgraded
    `DocumentViewerWidget` (Workspace destination, task 022) — both consume the
    same extracted `RichFilePreview` renderer; the existing
    `RichFilePreviewDialog` continues to wrap it for modal use cases. Per R5
    CLAUDE.md §3.1 reuse mandate: NO parallel preview renderer, NO parallel
    row-action menu.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior frontend engineer with Fluent UI v9 + React 19 expertise, deep
    familiarity with the `@spaarke/ai-widgets` Context-pane widget pattern
    (`PlaybookGalleryWidget`, `EntityInfoWidget`, `FindingsWidget`),
    `ContextWidgetRegistry` lazy-factory registration, the
    `useDispatchPaneEvent`/`usePaneEvent` PaneEventBus hooks, and the
    `DocumentRowMenu` 12-action contract.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `FilePreviewContextWidget.tsx` is committed to
    `src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/widgets/context/` and exports a
    default `ContextWidgetComponent<FilePreviewContextData>` that satisfies
    these acceptance criteria:
    (1) Single-file mode (`files.length === 1`) renders the file inline using
    the extracted `RichFilePreview` renderer (iframe + metadata + prev/next
    controls hidden when N=1 + 3-dot `DocumentRowMenu`).
    (2) Multi-file mode (`files.length &gt; 1`) renders a vertical list of
    Fluent v9 file cards above the active preview; clicking a card sets that
    file active and dispatches `context.file_selected` to the `context` channel
    via `useDispatchPaneEvent`.
    (3) Per-file 3-dot menu uses `DocumentRowMenu` (12 actions in canonical
    order); `aiSummary`, `toggleWorkspace`, `findSimilar` dispatch to the
    correct PaneEventBus channels / host callback; non-applicable actions are
    passed via `disabledActions`.
    (4) Widget is registered in `register-context-widgets.ts` with type string
    `'file-preview'` using the lazy-factory pattern that mirrors
    `playbook-gallery` / `entity-info` / `findings`.
    (5) Dark-mode parity verified (Fluent v9 semantic tokens only; zero
    hard-coded hex/rgb).
    (6) Loading + empty + error states render gracefully (never a blank pane).
    (7) Existing subscribers ignore the new `context.file_selected` event
    (additive type already validated by task 016).
    (8) `code-review` + `adr-check` quality gates pass at Step 9.5.
  </goal>

