  <constraints>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md §3.1">REUSE MANDATE — MUST wrap the extracted `RichFilePreview` renderer (task 013) for inline preview. MUST NOT rebuild iframe/metadata/prev-next/menu UI. MUST reuse `DocumentRowMenu` (12 actions) for the 3-dot menu. NO parallel file-preview component to `RichFilePreviewDialog`.</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md §3.4">PaneEventBus channels are closed at 4 per ADR-030. The widget uses ONLY the existing `context` channel and dispatches the additive `context.file_selected` event type added by task 016. NO new channel.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-021">Fluent UI v9 semantic tokens only — zero hard-coded hex/rgb. Dark-mode parity by construction. Loading state uses Fluent v9 `Skeleton`. Empty state renders meaningful affordance (never blank pane). Pattern: mirror `PlaybookGalleryWidget` styles.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-022">React 19 functional components. Hooks only — no class components. NOT PCF-safe (this widget runs in the SpaarkeAi Code Page shell, not PCF).</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-012">New code lives in `@spaarke/ai-widgets` (widget) + reuses `@spaarke/ui-components` (`RichFilePreview`, `DocumentRowMenu`). Component library boundaries respected.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-030">Additive event-type discipline — `context.file_selected` is a new discriminant on the existing `context` channel. Existing subscribers MUST ignore unknown types and continue functioning (no breakage of citation-highlight, entity-update, etc.).</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-018">R5 introduces NO new feature flags. The widget is registered unconditionally in `register-context-widgets.ts`. No `if (flag)` registration blocks.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec FR-08">"Summarize this only" per-file affordance is wired in task 021 (D2-12); this task creates the per-file card UI surface that task 021 extends. Keep the per-file card component composable (extract a `FilePreviewCard` sub-component) so task 021 can add the affordance without rewriting markup.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec NFR-02">ChatSession.UploadedFiles hard cap = 20 files. Multi-file list MUST handle up to 20 cards without performance degradation. Pattern: virtualization not required at N≤20; basic vertical flex list is acceptable.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec NFR-07 / ADR-029">BFF publish-size — this task is frontend-only. Confirm `dotnet publish` delta = 0 MB in task notes (no BFF code changed).</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Widget registry type string is `'file-preview'` (matches BFF widget payload key). If the BFF emits a different key during integration, surface the mismatch in task notes and request alignment — do NOT silently rename.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Per-file 3-dot menu hides `preview` action (the widget IS the preview); other irrelevant actions (e.g. `rename` if no handler) are passed via `disabledActions` per `DocumentRowMenu` contract.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">When `files.length === 0`, render an empty state ("No files attached") — never a blank pane. When `error` prop set, render the error inline using Fluent v9 `MessageBar`.</constraint>
  </constraints>

